news.title: GNIDA offers housing plots near Noida airport, one costs ₹152 crore
news.para: The Authority has put three prime plots on the auction block through e-bidding — 18,215sqm in Sector Mu with a reserve price of Rs 97 crore, a 30,000sqm plot in Sigma III with a reserve price of Rs 152 crore, and a 3,999sqm land parcel in Alpha II with a base price of Rs 25 crore.

news.title: Delhi CM proposes lower amalgamation charges, green building expansion
news.para: Gupta also reviewed the green building policy, directing that it be broadened beyond commercial structures to cover residential properties as well.

news.title: About 250 homes on government radar for building code violations in Gurugram's Sushant Lok 3
news.para: A 12-member enforcement team, led by district town planner (enforcement) Amit Madholia, has served notices to nearly 250 houses in Sushant Lok 3 for violating building norms and land use regulations.

news.title: Flats cancelled, Amrapali buyers protest at court receiver’s office in Noida
news.para: The protesters alleged their flats were cancelled and later awarded to other players at a very low cost to make money. "The buyers were not given a chance to submit their representation," they alleged. Attempts to contact Gaur builder and NBCC for their comments failed.

news.title: Five G+6 towers near Kolkata airport on AAI radar again after Gujarat tragedy
news.para: They have turned their focus on a high-rise complex at Bablatala, which is right across the airport wall, claiming the two top floors of the five towers pose a risk.

news.title: Home prices dip 3.5% in China in May 2025
news.para: New home prices fell 0.2% month-on-month in May after showing no growth the previous month, according to Reuters calculations based on data released by China's National Bureau of Statistics (NBS).

news.title: Godrej Properties to develop 14-acre land parcel in Hoskote, Bengaluru
news.para: The proposed development is expected to offer approximately 1.5 million sq ft of saleable area with an estimated revenue potential of ₹1,500 crore.

news.title: DLF to invest ₹5,500 crore to build housing project in Gurugram
news.para: According to sources, the company will soon launch an 18-acre project 'DLF Privana North' in Sector 76/77 Gurugram, comprising more than 1,150 apartments.

news.title: New PCMC initiative to rank housing societies that promote eco-friendly living in Pimpri Chinchwad
news.para: The stated aim of the ‘Green Society Initiative' is to rate and reward societies based on their performance across multiple areas — waste segregation, in-house composting, solar energy adoption, rainwater harvesting and wastewater recycling.

news.title: Thane metro line V extension on cards to ease pressure off local trains
news.para: With the aim of reducing crowd in local trains, Kalyan Lok Sabha MP Shrikant Shinde called a meeting of senior officials of MMRDA in which it was decided to extend Metro Line 5, which is coming up to Kalyan from Thane via Bhiwandi, further to Ambernath via Ulhasnagar.

news.title: Work yet to start, but Gurugram metro project cost is nearly double
news.para: The 28.5km corridor — planned to connect Millennium City Centre (MCC) and Cyber City with a spur to Dwarka Expressway — has faced multiple challenges since its conception.

news.title: Pune metro line III timeline extended to March 2026
news.para: The concessionaire's request for a deadline extension was placed before the committee and has now received formal approval, PMRDA commissioner Yogesh Mhase confirmed to TOI on Saturday.

news.title: Noida authority approves luxury hotels to boost business near airport
news.para: Noida Authority board, in its meeting on Saturday, approved a proposal to allot land for five- and seven-star hotels, to serve the demand generated by the upcoming Noida International Airport and IT and industrial hubs.

news.title: ED flags deep conspiracy in Bhoodan land case; top officials, bizmen under lens
news.para: The central agency, in its counter-affidavit, claimed land sales registered in survey numbers 181, 182, 194, and 195, including 50 acres of Bhoodan land, were executed without valid ownership by the sellers. The buyers reportedly include senior bureaucrats and businessmen.

news.title: Telangana raises alarm over Centre’s draft registration bill
news.para: Among the most contentious issues are proposed caps on registration charges and the move toward full online registration, which the state says may open the door to fraud and impersonation.

news.title: Ludhiana Improvement Trust areas transferred to civic body await development
news.para: While the LIT has given up control of these areas, the MC is yet to take over. In SBS Nagar, residents complain that no one has talked about resolving the City Centre issue.

news.title: US firms contribute 33% of total office demand in India's top 7 cities in 2022-24: JLL
news.para: Out of this, US firms have taken 64.5 million sq ft office spaces on rent, mainly to set up their Global Capability Centers (GCCs). Nearly 70 pc or 64.5 million square feet office spaces were rented for setting up of GCCs.

news.title: Delhi CM forms panel to revise circle rates
news.para: This decision was taken at a high-level meeting with the task force to discuss issues related to better infrastructure in the capital, ease of doing business, unauthorised colonies, housing societies, redevelopment of colonies and modernisation of infrastructure in industrial zones.
